Description: Bust to right, laureate. Wears cuirass. (obverse)
Eusebia of city standing to left, veiled, wears modius. With right hand drops incense on altar, left hand hidden in folds of peplos, in priestly guise. (reverse)
Bibliographic references: BMC Greek (Alexandria) / Catalogue of the coins of Alexandria and the Nomes (2511, p.324)
